@node section1 "What is Amiquote?"

                     @{b}What is Amiquote Pro?@{ub}

Amiquote is a door for MAXs BBS software. What it does is allow your users to
enter a message which will be displayed to all the following callers until
someone else decides to enter a message. The reason I created this door was
that most BBS software had something similar, for example Remote Access can
use Icenote and such. MAXs BBS lacked something similar of decent quality and
so came forth the creation of Amiquote. Amiquote is the product of months of
programming, late nights, loads of gurus and important work that's
been neglected! :).

Amiquote is freely distributable. Copy it, spread it, eat it or whatever.
Although this software is freely distributable the copyright remains with
the author Ian Chapman. No charge may be made for this software except to
cover the cost of the media on which the software is stored or the cost of
a phone call if the software is transmitted electronically. Please do not
distribute this software if it is incomplete, i.e. there are missing 
@{ "files in the archive" LINK section2}

@{b}Disclaimer@{ub}


We accept no responsibility for any damage to your system that this program
may cause (almost impossible that it will, gotta say these things though,
:) ), use this program at your own risk. Using this software will be taken
as an agreement of all the above terms.
@endnode

@node section2 "Files in the archive"

These files should be present in the Amiquote archive.

@{b}Amireader@{ub}       -  The door that reads and displays the message
@{b}Amiwriter@{ub}       -  The door that writes and creates the message
@{b}Message.txt@{ub}     -  An example message to get the door started
@{b}Amiquote.Guide@{ub}  -  This Amiga Guide document file.
@{b}Swear.txt@{ub}       -  ANSI swear screen! Pleaze change it!
@{b}Wordlist.txt@{ub}    -  List of Swear Words for Detection
@endnode

@node section3 "Installation on MAXs BBS"

                      @{b}Installation on Maxs BBS@{ub}

You @{b}MUST@{ub} have the following:

A directory with the assigned name of DOORS:
A directory in the DOORS: assignment called Nextcaller
A directory called  LOGFILES  in the  BBS:  Assignment

How to install.

All files should be placed in the following path:-

DOORS:Nextcaller/

This door comes in 2 parts the first part "Amireader" should be run when a
user logs on and the 2nd part "Amiwriter" should be an option from a menu,
I suggest the logoff menu.

Create a textfile called Maindoor.text in your DOORS: assignment, and add
the following, if this file already exists then just append the following
on a new line.

Nextcaller/Amireader

This is the script that will make sure the door is run on logon. Next
choose where you want the message editor to be run from, select the
appropriate menu from the menus editor within MAXs and enter the following.

KEY:  FUNCTION:  EXTRA:  LO ACC:  HI ACC:  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 M       34        0       20      10000   DOORS:Nextcaller/Amiwriter

You may choose which ever key you think is appropriate, it MUST be run with
function 34 as this is the MAXs function for running an external door. The
lo access and hi access are up to you but I suggest you only allow
validated users to use it. 

Once you've done this save the config and edit your ANSI menu to display
the Key that will run the door.

SWEAR.TXT
---------

This is just an ANSI warning screen that will be displayed to users who
abuse the door by swearing (if you have swear word detection on and that
swear word is in the list). This file must be present!

WORDLIST.TXT
------------
This file is a list of the words that you want to be detected by Amiquote.
An example looks like this (except for the numbers & colons)

1: 7
2: NO
3: FUCK
4: SHIT
5: WANK
6: CUNT
7: BITCH
8: SLAG
9: WANKER


Line 1
------
This tells Amiquote how many words you want Amiquote to detect, entering a
false number may cause Amiquote to hang.

Line 2
------
This tells Amiquote whether you want to enable swear word detection or not.
Enter YES if you do, enter NO if you don't!

Line 3 --> Onwards
------------------
These are the words which you want Amiquote to detect. The maximum is 50
and each word must be on a seperate line!

@endnode

@node section4 "Installation on Other Paragon BBS"

            @{b}Installation on Paragon compatible BBS software@{ub}

Sorry, this version of AmiQuote doesn't work on Paragon BBS systems :(
The reason is, the new editor uses maxs specific commands. Please look
for an earlier version (before Professional) for your BBS.

If you want the new features of the Pro version, and you run a Paragon
compatible BBS, contact either me or Ian, and we'll see what we can do...
@endnode

@node USING "Using Amiquote."


                         @{b}Using Amiquote@{ub}

Amireader displays the message and this is fairly self explanatory.
It displays the message which may be up to 15 lines high and 70 characters
wide, along with the name of the user that left the message.

Upon running Amiwriter the whole door is really self explanatory, the first
menu you are present with the following:

@{b}INTRO MENU:@{ub}

E) Enter a Message.

Goes to the message editor where the user can enter their message.

R) Read the current Message

Allows the user to view the current message, where the message is
displayed in all its glory. 

Q) Quit back to the BBS.

Guess! :-)       (uuuuuuuuhhhh....... give up. @{b}Pete@{ub} ;)

@{b}THE EDITOR:@{ub}

The editor allows up to 15 lines of text to be entered, it also allows up
to 70 characters per line to be typed. The user can edit command mode by
typing * on a blank line. Then they can press S to save or quit, U to go
up a line, C to continue or T to start again. If a user uses a percent
symbol (%) it will be replaced with "/" as MAXs uses % symbols for Auto
inserts and commands, for example if MAXs receives a %X it will log a user
off so this has obvious consequences. Should a user swear, or use a percent
symbol they will be warned and sent back to the INTRO MENU (if you have
swear word detection enabled. Upon finishing their message they get a choice
of whether they want to send it or not.

@{b}ADVERB MENU:@{ub}

This menu was added for fun rather than anything, it allows the user to
select an Adverb or to make one of their own. This is then displayed when
Amireader is run. 

e.g.

Joe Bloggs happily left this message:-

               OR

John Smith drunkenly left this message:-  etc ect.

@{b}COLOUR MENU:@{ub}

This menu allows the user to choose what colour they would like their
message to be displayed in. The Raidnbow option allows the users message to be
displayed with each line a different colour and the Scroll option means
that each line scrolls up from the bottom of the scren randomly changing
colour! Very nice effect!

Once the message has been saved in the file Message.txt in the path
DOORS:Nextcaller/   Amiquote also writes the users name, to a logfile which
can be used for the Sysops reference. It also stores the date and time and
whether the user tried to abuse the door or not.
This info is stored in the file BBS:logfiles/Amiquote.Log

@endnode

@node section6 "Version Notes"


                       @{b}Amiquote Version Notes@{ub}

@{b}Version 1.0@{ub}

Never released, bugs found when users added commas in their messages.
Limit of only 6 lines.
Limit of 50 chars per line.

@{b}Version 1.5@{ub}

Added comma detection, no longer allows you to use commas.
Added % symbol detection as MAXs uses these as Auto inserts.
Added detection of swear words.
Warns users if they use any of the above.
Added an option for the computer to choose a colour randomly for the
message to be displayed in, along with the other choices of colour.

V@{b}ersion 2.6@{ub}

Complete cosmetic face lift, especially with Amireader, now looks much more
professional.
Users now have up to 15 lines
Users have to to 70 chars.
Users can save their message at anytime by entering *S on a blank line.
Automatically stores users Name, Date & Time in a logfile.
Now detects more swear words.
Removed random colour choice and added a Multicolour choice where each line
is displayed in a different colour.
Added ADVERB choice for a bit of fun, users can select a word or write
their own.
Document now in Amigaguide Format.


V@{b}ersion 3.2@{ub}

This will be the last update as I have begun to find the coding of Amiquote
more of a chor.
Doesn't store the date & Time anymore
Added the scroll option
Replaces "," with "."
Replaces "%" with "/"
Allows you to design an optional ANSI screen which is displayed should a
user swear
Probably one or two other items aswell!
Removed a bug which opens a small window at the bottom!

V@{b}ersion 1.0 Pro@{ub}

Update by Peter Gordon, as Ian is too lazy! (see above)
Users can now use true commas
Far better editor/menus
File handling is much better
The code has been cleaned up A LOT, so it should be easier to update
(Never released used mainly as a beta on my BBS [Ian])

V@{b}ersion 1.1 Pro@{ub}
- Changed name to JZ Amiquote Pro to keep inline with my other doors! :)
- Now Logs Date & Time Once again! :)
- Allows the detection of swearing to be turned ON/OFF
- Sysop can configure the words that are detected
- Warns with an Orange Guru Alert if it can't find it's files!
- Amireader will display a message on itself if it can't find
  Message.txt instead of hanging.
- Menus looked improved greatly
- All menus a controlled by hotkeys now


@endnode

@node section7 "Other Doors"

                                @{b}Other Doors@{ub}

OTHER DOORS BY IAN CHAPMAN

JZ RAW DL - A RAW download door that allows you, the Sysop to send files
            that aren't online to any of your users. Brings up a requestor
            on the WB screen where you can select the file for download.
            MAXs BBS only.
             

RemoteRAWDL - Allows users to RAW download any file off your BBS with you
              needing to be involved! So if you are abscent and they need
              a file they can type in the pathname and DL it. Only
              reccomended to give Co-Sysops access to this door.
              MAXs BBS only.

Timegen - Run it on logon on and a user had a 5:1 chance of winning, should
          they do then they are randomly credited with an amount of time      
          ranging ffrom 1-60 mins. Just a bit of fun!
          MAXs and Paragon BBSs!

Athome - Displays whether you are IN or OUT to your users on logon which
         you can select via a menu option


JZ Pager - The ultimate pager for Maxs!
         - Allows the user to select between 20 music modules to page you
           with, or just the standard beep
         - Configurable ANSI screens
         - Choose the length of the Pager Bar!
         - Choose the character the Pager Bar uses!
         - Choose the speed of the pager Bar
         - Asks users for a reason
         - If you're in or busy, asks users if they wanna leave a message
         - Logs users name, reason, date & time!

MR Lotto - Chooses between 40 lottery machines
         - Computer gets 6 balls, user gets 6 balls, depending on the
           of matches the user gets credited with time.

OTHER DOORS BY PETER GORDON

KAWall - A good wall, but watch out for v2.....

KAPager - * Scrolly messages
          * Plays a MED mod or beeps
          * Keeps log
          * Opens a window

KAChat - *COMING SOON* This superb chat program will have features previously
         unheard of in MAXs chat programs.... Auto inserts, line wrap, split
         screen, log keeping, etc. etc.
@endnode

